## Client Management & Transaction System


This program is a C++ console application that manages client records stored in a text file (Clients.txt) and provides full CRUD operations along with basic banking transactions.

Features

Store client information using a struct (strInfo) including:

Name, Account Number, PinCode, Phone, Salary

Load all clients into a vector for easy management.

CRUD Operations:

Add new clients with unique account numbers

Update existing client information

Delete clients safely with confirmation

Find and display client details

Transactions:

Deposit money into a client’s account

Withdraw money with validation

Display total salaries of all clients

File handling ensures that data is persistent and deleted clients are properly removed from the file.

Simple text-based menu system for navigation between main menu and transaction menu.

Learning Points

This project is great for practicing:

Structs and vectors

File I/O in C++

String parsing and conversion

Safe delete/update operations

User input handling and basic validation

Building a text-based menu-driven console application

